  "doc_id": "5822",
  "text": "By 4 dpi, the type and severity of lesions in the lung and nasal cavity were similar for both Nipah virus isolates. Although disease progression was initially more rapid for NiV-B, by 4 dpi, both Nipah virus isolates caused essentially the same severity of pulmonary and nasal cavity lesions in Syrian hamsters. Similarly, in ferrets oronasally inoculated with NiV-B or NiV-M, the clinical respiratory signs and respiratory tract histologic lesions were comparable. [CITATION_1] Intraperitoneal inoculation of Syrian hamsters with NiV-B or NiV-M also did not result in differences in lesion severity between the 2 isolates, although disease onset and lesion development were faster with NiV-M than with NiV-B. [CITATION_2] However, all studies to date comparing NiV-M and NiV-B have used the same 2 isolates, and the results would be strengthened if these studies could be repeated using virus isolates from different outbreaks in Bangladesh.",
